\name{xkcd-package}
\alias{xkcd-package}
\alias{xkcd}
\docType{package}
\title{
Plot ggplot graphics in a XKCD style
}
\description{
  XKCD is a webcomic of romance, sarcasm, math, and language created by
  Randall Munroe. This package tries to give a satisfactory answer to
  the question How can we make xkcd style graphs in R?. The package
  provides a set of ggplot2 functions for plotting data in a XKCD style.
}
\details{
\tabular{ll}{
Package: \tab xkcd\cr
Type: \tab Package\cr
Version: \tab 0.0.1\cr
Date: \tab 2013-04-27\cr
License: \tab GPL3\cr
}
This package introduces two main functions: \command{man} and
\command{segment}. The \command{man} function creates a xkcd man and the
\command{segment} one plots pseudo handwritten segments. Both functions
are derived from the \command{geom_path} of the package
ggplot. Therefore, you can use all the funcionalities of the ggplot system. See
the vignette for detailed examples.
}
